* — Guards the `ALTER TABLE ... ADD COLUMN email TEXT` with a `PRAGMA table_info` check, so running it twice no longer errors (`ALTER TABLE ADD COLUMN` fails if the column exists). Rows are untouched; the new column is nullable.\n\n**`downgrade(conn)`** — Replaced the destructive `DROP TABLE users` (which lost all data) with `ALTER TABLE users DROP COLUMN email`, guarded by a column-existence check. This removes only the `email` column while preserving all `id`/`name` rows, and is also idempotent.\n\nA small `_columns(conn)` helper avoids duplicating the `PRAGMA` introspection. No tests were modified."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"zai-coding-cn","model":"glm-5.2","usage":{"input":239,"output":200,"cacheRead":5248,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":5687,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782143789317,"responseId":"20260622235631d89c051c380147e8"}],"willRetry":false}
